category":"marriage","header":"Married British Army officer Prevost at seventeen","body":"She married Jacques Marcus Prevost — a British Army officer eighteen years her senior — at age seventeen, around 1763. Five children followed before his 1781 death made her a thirty-five-year-old widow with five young Prevost-line children still in the Hermitage household."},{"number":3,"category":"marriage","header":"Aaron Burr remarried her after Prevost's death","body":"Aaron Burr Jr — who had stayed at the Hermitage as a young officer during the Revolution — married her on 2 July 1782, less than a year after Prevost's death. Their daughter Theodosia Burr Alston was lost at sea in 1813, a wound Burr carried for the rest of his life."},{"number":4,"category":"death","header":"Died of cancer at forty-seven, before Hamilton duel","body":"She died of stomach or uterine cancer at New York on 18 May 1794 at age forty-seven. The death came a decade before Burr's 1804 duel with Hamilton; she was spared seeing her husband become the era's most controversial political figure."}],"slug":"theodosia-bartow-1746"}},"burialCemetery":null,"institutionsById":{},"crossConnections":[]}